title: Starbase orbital duo preps for Static Fire campaign – KSC Starship Progress
summary: SpaceX’s Starbase is heading into its latest phase of milestones for Starship, with the high likelihood the FAA is close to approving a critical checkpoint for its rapidly reusable launch vehicle, paving the way for the orbital launch attempt of Booster 7 with Ship 24.

title: Egypt’s Nilesat 301 passes health checks after SpaceX launch
summary: Egyptian operator NileSat’s latest communications satellite is ready to move to its final orbit after clearing health checks following its SpaceX launch June 8, according to the spacecraft’s prime contractor.

title: Space Force delivers first of two U.S. payloads to launch on Space Norway’s arctic broadband mission
summary: The U.S. Space Force delivered the first of two military communications payloads that will launch in 2023 on Space Norway’s Arctic Satellite Broadband Mission.

title: NASA to Discuss New Unidentified Aerial Phenomena Study Today
summary: NASA will host a media teleconference at 1 p.m. EDT today – Thursday, June 9 –  to discuss a new study team the agency is commissioning to examine unidentified aerial phenomena (UAPs).
